<br>
Only problem is the Left will just see all the attempts to tell them that people must do for themselves as some evil plot to deny them (the left) from ordering the rest of us around.<br>
<br>
I love when the complaint is that somehow the system takes from the poor and less fortunate and that the solution to that is to forceable remove the wealth from those that have it to give to others.... UMM excuse me? Werent you JUST complaining that YOU didnt want what you earned/had taken away from YOU?<br>
<br>
How is it &quot;fair&quot; to take MORE (percentage wise) from someone because they were able to make more? <br>
<br>
I can see NOT taking from some people because they cant afford to be taxed.  We already have that in the Tax laws. But to take a higher percentage from people that earn more simply breeds the effort to AVOID paying at all.<br>
<br>
You are saying , in effect, that we are going to punish you for being able to earn more. <br>
<br>
Taking from others forceably is wrong, doesnt matter if you are taking from the rich or the poor. And without Capitalism..... exactly how do we determine who gets what? Who gets to distribute the wealth? Who gets to decide who does what? And a HOST of other questions.<br>
<br>
Now dont get me wrong.... it would be nice for the world if we lived in a society were everyone had ALL their basic needs met, but even then there will be those with and those without.<br>
<br>
NO other system works (or none has anyway) on a Scale of the Governments around now.<br>
<br>
The Government of the United States of America is the only Government that promotes individual Freedom. It is (in my opinion) the best Government on Earth right now. <br>
<br>
To throw it out because it has flaws is not very bright. What exactly are you going to replace it with? Name a country or government that HAS proven to work and hasnt the flaws you are attacking.<br>
<br>
More importantly, remember that in this government it is possible to effect change and it is possible to address wrongs openly. It is not easy , the founding fathers made the Government a slow unweilding beast for a reason. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zsuzsanadracul>Zsuzsana Dracul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/01 6:46:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=95.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: How did Adolf Hitler get so much darn power?</span><hr size=1> Sorry I did not get in here until very late <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
